Wonderful, tasty, delicious food! Made from scratch, what else can someone want/need?

Scratch made brunch in a bag..how could this not be great. Everyone talks about New York bagels. I guess that's because they haven't had the home made bagels from Early to Rise (ETR).  Those with the house smoked salmon and brunch is ready to go. At $28 a bag it's an unbelievably good way to support local and enjoy a great Sunday!
Beautiful and great food. Loved it here.

It feels so good to be back in my home town! BAY CITY YOU ARE BEAUTIFUL! And, this California Girl is proud to support my friends at Early to Rise! Crab and Eggs Benedict with a strong Americano! A gorgeous sunrise and my smile ear to ear! …
Amazing! We had the bagel takeout kit with lox and it was one of the best brunch experiences in SF.

I look forward to Friday so I can place my early to rise order. The last batch of bagels was highly impressive. The bagels have evolved into a fine art with fluff and flavor. The doughnuts are equally impressive and although their …
Simply put, best bagel in SF.
Delicious. I had a zesty pork and pepper hash and a donut that was perfectly understated.
ETR is the stuff breakfast dreams are made of!

🥯Bagels are incredible, chewy and delicious with so much flavor! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ We also tried the crab eggs benedict: so fresh and delicious, from the 🥑 to the light, creamy Hollandaise style sauce. 🦀🦀🦀🦀 🥯The smoked salmon on the lox …

Loved the outdoor brunch experience just as much as I loved the pop-up! Freshly made bagels and donuts, and probably the best shrimp and grits I’ve ever had. My fave brunch of 2020 - thanks Chef Andrew!
Incredible assortment of breakfast foods.  My wife and I thoroughly enjoyed the take-home bagels and lox breakfast with doughnuts :)

This place is a treasure to be experienced, not missed! Savory, delicious with gracious and attentive service-can't wait to return a 3rd time and especially can't wait until we can eat family style again. Had Shrimp & Grits-the most satisfying meal I've had in months! Thank you EtR! oxo
The food keeps getting better every time we visit. 5 star brunch joint. Highly Recommended.
Delicious food, great Atmosphere

Very fun brunch experience. Loved meeting new folks and sharing an amazing meal together! Fun dishes and I absolutely recommend this place to everyone looking a for a fun switch up to a fixed course meal - BRUNCH TIME!

What a fantastic experience! The food was stellar...everything homemade in house. I think the bacon was the best I've ever had and we couldn't stop eating those bagels! Chef Andrew and his staff were charming and made everyone feel welcome. …
A unique experience and very delicious food. The french toast is THAT good! Highly recommend and if you come a little bit early you should be able to get priority type seating

We found this spot accidentally strolling by and scheduling a brunch there every weekend ever since.  The meal itself is great - pancakes, sausage, scramble eggs - everything is superb. But there is also short, but quite distinct selection …

The ambiance is welcoming and friendly, the price is great for the quality of food you're getting, and the food is outstanding. Everything is fresh, delicious, and made with care. Everyone working there is so friendly, and the chef is outstanding. Try it once and you'll be sold!

Phenomenal. Went with a group of six and all of us loved it. Easily the most memorable meal in a weekend and SF, and the family style ticketed seating was a great concept. The food was fast and just kept coming. We hugged the chef afterwards.
Great concept, delicious food and overall highly recommended experience. Highlight of our long weekend. Please go if you’re visiting San Francisco, or a local!

Awesome communal-table concept, great price for high end prix fixe, and killer food. Their circular breads (bagels & donuts alike) are particularly masterful! Reservations required, but that's great because it means no waiting in SF brunch lines!
Very good experience, the brunch was fresh and awesome! Andrew was very friendly and loved French wine which is a good thing :) I would definitely recommend it!
Delicious! Andrew and his staff were wonderful.
The food is soooo tasty! I love the freshness and authenticity of the menu.
This place is owned by food lovers. Walked in the restaurant and delightfully surprised by the wonderful dishes! Love love love.

By far my favorite brunch in SF. The bagels are fresh, warm, doughy and seedy, which is hard to beat. Plus the tomatoes are sliced to fit perfectly on the bagel to make a lox sandwich. Save room for the eggs and bacon!
This is definitely one of the best brunch so far. The staff was friendly and efficient. And they had extra food if you were really hungry. Like Arnold said "I'll be back"
So tasty! And reasonably priced for all that food!

Absolutely phenomenal. Very reasonably priced for a 5 course brunch, and only $15 extra dollars to get unlimited Greyhound cocktails. Chef Andrew's food is to die for, and was honestly one of the best meals I've had in my life.

Very great experience - my vegetarian friend came for the bagel and lox brunch, and Andrew prepared a special vegetarian dish for him. Food was absolutely delicious (great bagels!!), and the special attention from the chef was a great touch. Have recommended it to all my friends the day after!

Excellent, unique brunch! We had grits with shrimp and mushroom along with a few more courses - everything was delicious, plentiful and fresh, chef Andrew is passionate about food and it shows in every dish. Looking forward to going back and hope the grits are back in rotation soon! :)

Love love loved ETR. Incredible bagels (made fresh that morning) with seasonal tomatoes and salmon, followed by the best bacon I've ever eaten, with scrambled eggs. Great coffee, and finished up with seasonal fresh fruit. The place was buzzing - food served family style; tickets must be bought in advance; BYOB.

Best brunch in SF so far! We booked the southern-inspired 1 PM brunch, which was so special to me as someone who just moved to SF from North Carolina. Every dish was fresh, flavorful and honest.

I found Early To Rise on Tock while searching through place to eat in San Francisco. The concept sounded unique and the menu looked good so we booked for a Saturday (pancakes) and Sunday (bagels/ lox). Our group couldn't have been happier …

Was looking for a spot to do a special brunch with my partner one Sunday afternoon and found this absolutely amazing place. Was so much fun and really a wholly different experience for us! Really loved the family-style and communal …

Gem of a place for a weekend brunch! The chef personally talks to everyone and other staff’s service is par excellence. The food was awesome and fresh. Very casual setting. Definitely a good morning start for a weekend day!
Not only a delicious brunch, but excellent service with lovely staff and a charming setting. The shrimp and grits option was excellent—can’t wait to try the other menu options.
Best brunch in the city. Every dish is made with care, and just chatting with the chef, you can feel his excitement in sharing his love of cooking with everyone.
Fantastic atmosphere, delicious food and the Greyhound s are delicious. Chef comes to the tables and pours on the charm. A must!
So good!! Lovely chef who was amazingly kind and accommodating to our birthday group and special dietary needs.  I would come back as often as I can.

Great brunch! Flavor and quality was wonderful! Plenty of food with several refills on dishes. Makes for a memorable experience! Chef introduced himself and the vision for the menu. Easy to sit with group if you arrive just ten minutes …
I had an excellent Eggs Blackstone brunch here over the weekend. Its great fun to sit family style and the food is delicious. Extra points for making things like the hot sauce from scratch.
The dishwasher at this place is amazing! Never seen porcelain so bright!

Spectacular brunch. We joined the 1pm seating, to experience the 5 dishes meal. It was an amazing experience, the beautiful dishes are all made from scratch and while everything was served family style, we easily got seconds if needed/wanted. You can tell the chef truly loves what he does.

This place is passionate about making good food and good experiences. The family style allows you to meet new people and share a delicious meal. The chef talks to everyone to explain the dishes, his inspiration, and asks for question and …

I've been to Andrews brunch over 20 times by this point. I'm loving this new spot and his menus never disappoint. Seasonal menus, well thought out, locally sourced, quality products cooked to a holy perfection. Eggs Stinson is maybe a all …

Part of me wants to keep this gem a secret. But everybody should get to try Andrew’s food at least once! The menu changes seasonally and always impresses. Eating here is a reminder that food can more than the sum of its ingredients, the atmosphere and shared experience is amazing.

If you have never been to a communal food event and if you don't want to wait in line for some mediocre brunch in SF, well, give this event a try! I bet you will not regret it. I have done 5-6 Feastly(communal food) events in the past, but …

Chef Andrew was awesome! You can really tell he cares about the experience! The meal was delicious and the staff was friendly and helpful with our wine etc. Chef came by at the end to talk to us and he was a pleasure to meet. Thanks again for the great experience! One of the best in the city for brunch — no wait, fair price, tasty food

Oh my.. where do I begin? Andrew is a food magician. I swear he has the Midas touch - every food item he touches turns into deliciousness. On top of that - the generosity typical of a Southern country lad also shows through. There were …
Great food and communal eating in a nice space. Staff were super friendly and fun.
Enjoyed a wonderful brunch here — it’s communal dining which creates a family-style experience. The food was delicious, and they accommodated my vegetarian needs. It’s worth the uphill climb!
I've been here twice and both times the food was amazing and the service was great. I will definitely be going back again.
The lox and bagels were extremely good, but the cream cheese was even better! Anyway, excellent breakfast.

I’ve been to both seatings and can only rave about the quality of food! Creamy eggs Benedict, smoky bacon, good coffee and the bagels are out of this world! Big portions, communal eating, very relaxed atmosphere and the staff are attentive. …
Everything about Andrews brunch is spectacular, all the way down to his house made hot sauce. His bagels & lox are better than anywhere in NYC.

Andrew’s Early to Rise brunch is one of the best deals in town. House made bagels, salmon lox and smear get out of here! If you are around Nob Hill on a Sunday make your way over to Jackson and Taylor, you won’t be disappointed!

What a great Sunday Brunch at Early to Rise. With fresh homemade bagels to start. Next creamy flavorful grits with seasoned vegetables, crab Benedict all yummy. Chef Andrews  delicious fresh twist on Ambrosia salad, can't wait to go back for more. I'm looking forward to my next brunch.
I love this place! So much good food for so little money! Greyhounds are one of the best I've ever had in my life. Will be bringing my birthday party here!

Friends brought me here after explaining the premise that everything was made in-house. Totally worth it, the smoked salmon and bagels were great, and the eggs were some of the best I've had! The "pass the plate around" family style way of serving was something I enjoyed and created a sense of community with your fellow diners.

booked this brunch on a whim, did not disappoint! best bagels and lox in san francisco
Chef Andrew's new venue is great and the food is as amazing as ever!
